The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 BRIEFS

 Burdwan, April 17: Burdwan chief medical officer Manjur Murshed was killed here this evening when a truck laden with LPG cylinders crashed into the car he was travelling in. 

 Murshed, 56, was returning from Calcutta after a meeting at the health headquarters in Salt Lake. The driver, Samir Guha, 40, was killed on the spot, while Murshed succumbed to injuries at Burdwan Medical College and Hospital.

 Burdwan: Twelve-year-old Pakhi Ghosh succumbed to burns in hospital on Monday night. The Class V student was charred in sleep when a slum in Manteswar, Burdwan, was gutted.

 Calcutta: CPM member of Parliament Basudeb Acharya was admitted to the intensive cardiac care unit of SSKM Hospital on Tuesday. A railway standing committee member, he took ill in Agartala while supervising a project there.

 Calcutta: Shantanu Manna of Baranagar in north Calcutta, and his parents were held after he took his wife to RG Kar Hospital on Tuesday night and claimed that she committed suicide. Police said neighbours accused Manna of torturing Deepshikha, 21. 




